query.description: This field is the equivalent to product type in the Treez UI. The value of the field describes the product type the inventory was assigned to when it was recieved.

The active parameter filters for active products in the product catalog. If this parameter is set to 'FALSE' only deactivated products will be returned in the response. If set to 'TRUE', only active products will be returned. If this parameter is set to 'ALL', it will return both active and deactivated products. Whether a product is active or not does not have any relationship with a product having inventory or not.
Filter by unique ID associated with each product. The product_id value will not change once a product has been created. You can search up to 50 product IDs at time with this endpoint.
This allows partners to filter for products in a particular location in Treez.
This parameter allows the partner to filter based on the inventory type of the product. The filters for this filter are MEDICAL, ADULT, and ALL.

When the parameter is set to 'TRUE' the response will only contain products that are above the minimum_visible_inventory_level set up in the config page of Treez. If 'FALSE' the products listed in the response will be below the minimum_visible_inventory_level.
Is the equivalent to product type in the treez UI. The value of the field describes the product type the inventory was assigned to when it was received.

The active parameter filters for active products in the product catalog. If this parameter is set to 'FALSE' only deactivated products will be returned in the response. If set to 'TRUE', only active products will be returned. If this parameter is set to 'ALL', it will return both active and deactivated products. Whether a product is active or not does not have any relationship with a product having inventory or not.
